==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dryobalanops
<hw>Dry`o*bal"a*nops</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <grk>dry^s</grk> oak + <grk>ba`lanos</grk> acorn +
<grk>'o`psis</grk> appearance. The fruit remotely resembles an acorn in
its cup.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The genus to which belongs the
single species <spn>Dryobalanops Camphora</spn>, a lofty resinous tree
of Borneo and Sumatra, yielding Borneo camphor and camphor
oil.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

